The paper discusses the use of wearable sensors for affect recognition, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also covers machine learning methods for processing and classifying the data collected from the sensors, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of physiological measurements, which is related to cybernetics (cs.CY) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of wearable sensors for mental health applications, which is related to neuroscience (cs.NE).
